math.display.latex:

						\begin{array}{rcrcrcl}
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$a_1$}{\color{red} x} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$a_2$}{\color{red} y} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$a_3$}{\color{red} z} & = & {\color{blue} c} \\
\colorbox{lightgreen}{$b_1$}{\color{red} x} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$b_2$}{\color{red} y} & + & \colorbox{lightgreen}{$b_3$}{\color{red} z} & = & {\color{blue} d}
						\end{array}

para.para.body:
renders both equations true simultaneously if and only if 
                     \Vect{x}
                   belongs to the line of intersection of the two solution hyperplanes of the given equations.
